    "identifier": "PRJEB43407",
    "name": "Highfield Ley Arable - Metagenomic Study",
    "shortName": "METAGEN",
    "url": "https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ena/browser/view/PRJEB43407",
    "description": [
        {
            "inLanguage": "en",
            "descriptionType": "Abstract",
            "description": "The combination of longevity and the extremes of land use associated with the Highfield experiments mean that we can investigate the full extent of changes arising from management and test the limits of soil.  Applying modern techniques including shotgun metagenome sequencing, X-ray computed tomography and pore-scale hydrodynamic modelling reveals new insights into soil system behaviour, provides the knowledge base for a new theory of soil and  fundamental evidence to support farmers' decisions relating to soil management."
        },
        {
            "inLanguage": "en",
            "descriptionType": "Methods",
            "description": "Shotgun metagenomic sequence data from the Highfield Ley Arable and Highfield Bare Fallow experiments has been deposited with the European Nucleotide Archive.  For each of three treatments (permanent pasture, continuous winter wheat arable, and permanent bare fallow), three replicate datasets are available, each of 150 nucleotide base, paired-end read sequences generated on an Illumina sequencing platform."
        },
        {
            "inLanguage": "en",
            "descriptionType": "TechnicalInfo",
            "description": "Sequencing was provided by Illumina (Great Abington, U.K.) as part of the DeepSoil consortium, together with Rothamsted Research and the Pacific Northwest National Laboratory, Richland, Washington, USA."
        }
    ],
